HEADWORD: Cucumiform
<hw>Cu*cu"mi*form</hw> <pr>(k?-k?"m?-f?rm)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cucumis</ets> cucumber + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the
form of a cucumber; having the form of a cylinder tapered and rounded at
the ends, and either straight or curved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

